    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1819" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βαρύς</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εῖα, ύ</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">heavy</span>, oftener figurative than
          literal; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σχέθε χεῖρα βαρεῖαν</span>, stayed
          his ‘heavy hand,’ suggesting power, <i><span class="en">Il.
            1.219</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; βαρείᾱς χεῖρας ἐποίσει</span>, ‘violent’
          hands, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.89</span></i>; of ‘grievous’ pains,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 5.417</span></i>; ‘dread’ fates, <i><span class="en">Il. 21.548</span></i>; ‘low,’ ‘gruff’ voice, <i><span class="en">Od. 9.257</span></i>, etc.; adv., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βαρύ</span> and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">βαρέα
            στενάχειν</span>, sigh ‘deeply.’</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
